        <!-- Remuneration and Fees -->
        <section class="credit-section" id="remuneration">
            <div class="container">
                <h2>How We Are Remunerated</h2>
                <div class="content">
                    <h3>Commission-Based Model</h3>
                    <p>
                        We operate on a commission-based model where we receive payments from lenders when 
                        successful finance arrangements are established. This means our services are typically 
                        provided at no direct cost to you.
                    </p>

                    <div class="remuneration-details">
                        <div class="fee-category">
                            <h4>Upfront Commission</h4>
                            <p>
                                We receive an upfront commission from the lender when your loan settles. 
                                This commission is calculated as a percentage of the loan amount:
                            </p>
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Equipment Finance:</strong> 0.5% to 2.5% of loan amount</li>
                                <li><strong>Commercial Property:</strong> 0.6% to 1.2% of loan amount</li>
                                <li><strong>Working Capital:</strong> 1.0% to 3.0% of facility limit</li>
                                <li><strong>Personal Lending:</strong> 0.65% to 1.1% of loan amount</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>
                                <em>Commission rates vary based on loan type, lender, loan amount, and terms. 
                                Specific commission amounts will be disclosed in your quote.</em>
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="fee-category">
                            <h4>Trail Commission</h4>
                            <p>
                                For some loan products, we may receive ongoing trail commission 
                                throughout the life of the loan:
                            </p>
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Home Loans:</strong> 0.15% to 0.25% per annum of outstanding balance</li>
                                <li><strong>Some Commercial Facilities:</strong> 0.10% to 0.50% per annum</li>
                                <li><strong>Line of Credit Facilities:</strong> 0.25% to 0.75% per annum of limit</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>
                                Trail commission is paid by the lender and does not affect your interest rate or loan terms.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="fee-category">
                            <h4>Direct Fees (When Applicable)</h4>
                            <p>
                                In specific circumstances, we may charge direct fees for our services:
                            </p>
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Complex Structuring Fee:</strong> $2,500 to $15,000 for sophisticated commercial structures</li>
                                <li><strong>Due Diligence Fee:</strong> $1,500 to $5,000 for detailed financial analysis</li>
                                <li><strong>Documentation Review Fee:</strong> $500 to $2,000 for complex legal documentation</li>
                                <li><strong>Unsuccessful Application Fee:</strong> $500 to $2,500 (only if disclosed upfront)</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>
                                <strong>Important:</strong> Any direct fees will be clearly disclosed and agreed upon 
                                in writing before we commence work on your application.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <h3>Third-Party Payments</h3>
                    <p>
                        We may receive payments or benefits from third parties including:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Lender marketing and training events</li>
                        <li>Professional development and education programs</li>
                        <li>Technology platform and software subsidies</li>
                        <li>Industry conference and networking event support</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>
                        These benefits do not influence our credit assistance services or product recommendations, 
                        which are based on your specific needs and circumstances.
                    </p>

                    <div class="highlight-box">
                        <h4>Transparency Commitment</h4>
                        <p>
                            We are committed to full transparency about our remuneration. Before proceeding with 
                            any application, we will provide you with specific details of:
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Exact commission amounts we will receive</li>
                            <li>Any direct fees that may apply</li>
                            <li>Alternative remuneration structures available</li>
                            <li>How our remuneration may influence our recommendations</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Conflicts of Interest -->
        <section class="credit-section" id="conflicts">
            <div class="container">
                <h2>Conflicts of Interest</h2>
                <div class="content">
                    <h3>Managing Conflicts of Interest</h3>
                    <p>
                        We are committed to managing conflicts of interest to ensure our recommendations 
                        are in your best interests. We have policies and procedures to identify, 
                        manage, and disclose any potential conflicts.
                    </p>

                    <div class="conflict-categories">
                        <div class="conflict-type">
                            <h4>Remuneration-Based Conflicts</h4>
                            <p>
                                Different lenders may pay different commission rates, which could potentially 
                                influence our recommendations. To manage this conflict:
                            </p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>We maintain a diverse panel of lenders with competitive rates</li>
                                <li>Our recommendations are based on a comparison process considering your needs</li>
                                <li>We disclose commission rates before you sign any applications</li>
                                <li>We provide explanations for our recommendations beyond just commission</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>

                        <div class="conflict-type">
                            <h4>Lender Relationships</h4>
                            <p>
                                We maintain ongoing business relationships with multiple lenders. These relationships:
                            </p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Enable us to access competitive products and faster processing</li>
                                <li>May include volume-based incentives that we disclose transparently</li>
                                <li>Do not prevent us from recommending the most suitable lender for your needs</li>
                                <li>Are managed through our conflicts of interest policy</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>

                        <div class="conflict-type">
                            <h4>Related Entity Interests</h4>
                            <p>
                                We do not have ownership interests in any lending institutions. However:
                            </p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>We may have referral arrangements with professional service providers</li>
                                <li>Any financial interests in related businesses are disclosed</li>
                                <li>We maintain independence in our credit assistance services</li>
                                <li>Referrals to related entities are disclosed and optional</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <h3>Conflict Management Strategies</h3>
                    <p>When conflicts of interest arise, we manage them by:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Disclosure:</strong> Full disclosure of any relevant conflicts before providing advice</li>
                        <li><strong>Avoidance:</strong> Declining to act where conflicts cannot be managed appropriately</li>
                        <li><strong>Management:</strong> Implementing procedures to ensure conflicts don't compromise our advice</li>
                        <li><strong>Documentation:</strong> Recording conflicts and management strategies in your file</li>
                    </ul>

                    <div class="highlight-box">
                        <h4>Your Right to Know</h4>
                        <p>
                            You have the right to ask about any potential conflicts of interest that may 
                            affect our services. We encourage you to discuss any concerns about our 
                            recommendations or the basis for our advice.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Complaints Process -->
        <section class="credit-section" id="complaints">
            <div class="container">
                <h2>Complaints and Dispute Resolution</h2>
                <div class="content">
                    <h3>Internal Complaints Process</h3>
                    <p>
                        If you have a complaint about our credit services, we have an internal 
                        dispute resolution process to address your concerns promptly and fairly.
                    </p>

                    <div class="complaints-process">
                        <div class="step">
                            <div class="step-number">1</div>
                            <div class="step-content">
                                <h4>Lodge Your Complaint</h4>
                                <p>Contact us with your complaint using any of the following methods:</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li><strong>Phone:</strong> 1300 XXX XXX</li>
                                    <li><strong>Email:</strong> complaints@edgeviewfinance.com.au</li>
                                    <li><strong>Written:</strong> Post to our registered office</li>
                                    <li><strong>In Person:</strong> During business hours</li>
                                </ul>
                                <p>Please provide details of your complaint including relevant dates, documents, and your desired outcome.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="step">
                            <div class="step-number">2</div>
                            <div class="step-content">
                                <h4>Acknowledgment</h4>
                                <p>We will acknowledge your complaint within <strong>1 business day</strong> and provide:</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Confirmation we have received your complaint</li>
                                    <li>A reference number for tracking</li>
                                    <li>The name of the person handling your complaint</li>
                                    <li>Information about our complaints process</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="step">
                            <div class="step-number">3</div>
                            <div class="step-content">
                                <h4>Investigation</h4>
                                <p>We will investigate your complaint by:</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Reviewing all relevant documentation and records</li>
                                    <li>Consulting with relevant staff and systems</li>
                                    <li>Seeking additional information if required</li>
                                    <li>Considering applicable laws and industry standards</li>
                                </ul>
                                <p><strong>Timeframe:</strong> Most complaints are resolved within 21 days. Complex matters may take up to 45 days.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="step">
                            <div class="step-number">4</div>
                            <div class="step-content">
                                <h4>Resolution</h4>
                                <p>We will provide a written response including:</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Our findings and the reasons for our decision</li>
                                    <li>Any remedial action we will take</li>
                                    <li>Any compensation or corrective measures</li>
                                    <li>Information about external dispute resolution options</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <h3>External Dispute Resolution</h3>
                    <p>
                        If you are not satisfied with our internal resolution, or if we do not 
                        respond within 45 days, you can lodge a complaint with the Australian 
                        Financial Complaints Authority (AFCA).
                    </p>

                    <div class="external-complaints">
                        <div class="external-option">
                            <h4>Australian Financial Complaints Authority (AFCA)</h4>
                            <div class="contact-info">
                                <p><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://www.afca.org.au" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.afca.org.au</a></p>
                                <p><strong>Phone:</strong> 1800 931 678</p>
                                <p><strong>Email:</strong> info@afca.org.au</p>
                                <p><strong>Post:</strong> Australian Financial Complaints Authority<br/>
                                GPO Box 3, Melbourne VIC 3001</p>
                            </div>
                            <p>
                                AFCA is a free service established by the Australian Government to 
                                resolve complaints about financial services. AFCA can make determinations 
                                that are binding on us, but not on you.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="external-option">
                            <h4>Australian Securities and Investments Commission (ASIC)</h4>
                            <div class="contact-info">
                                <p><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://www.asic.gov.au" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.asic.gov.au</a></p>
                                <p><strong>Phone:</strong> 1300 300 630</p>
                                <p><strong>Online:</strong> ASIC Report Misconduct page</p>
                            </div>
                            <p>
                                ASIC regulates our credit licence and can investigate breaches 
                                of credit legislation and licensing conditions.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="highlight-box">
                        <h4>No Cost Complaints Service</h4>
                        <p>
                            Our internal complaints handling service is provided at no cost to you. 
                            AFCA's service is also free. You may wish to seek independent legal 
                            advice, though this is at your own cost.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Privacy Information -->
        <section class="credit-section" id="privacy">
            <div class="container">
                <h2>Privacy and Personal Information</h2>
                <div class="content">
                    <h3>How We Handle Your Information</h3>
                    <p>
                        We collect, use, and disclose personal information (including credit information) 
                        in accordance with the Privacy Act 1988 and the Credit Reporting Privacy Code 2014.
                    </p>

                    <div class="privacy-summary">
                        <div class="privacy-item">
                            <h4>Information Collection</h4>
                            <p>We collect personal information including:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Identity and contact information</li>
                                <li>Financial and employment details</li>
                                <li>Credit information from credit reporting bodies</li>
                                <li>Information from referees and other sources</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>

                        <div class="privacy-item">
                            <h4>Information Use</h4>
                            <p>We use your information to:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Assess your credit needs and borrowing capacity</li>
                                <li>Recommend suitable credit products</li>
                                <li>Submit applications to lenders</li>
                                <li>Manage our ongoing relationship with you</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>

                        <div class="privacy-item">
                            <h4>Information Disclosure</h4>
                            <p>We may disclose your information to:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Credit providers and their representatives</li>
                                <li>Credit reporting bodies</li>
                                <li>Professional service providers</li>
